Comments:
---------
The timely intervention in Mali and Niger
highlights that the subdivision of large
districts in sub-districts of less than 100 000
inhabitants (ref. definition of intervention
thresholds) allows a timely detection of an
emerging epidemic, the laboratory confirmation of
germs and undertake rapid control and prevention measures.

